  "number": 859,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/859",
  "title": "Allow specifying the searchBox form (submit button, reset button)",
  "body": "It would be nice, for mobile experience for example, to be able to link the searchBox to a form so that we only search when the form is submitted.\n\nWhat do you think?\n\nIt kind of look like the searchOnlyOnEnterKey option but with a form and maybe an `<input type=\"submit\" />`\n\nThis could be done this way:\n\n``` js\nsearchBox({\n  inputContainer: // the input to target, mandatory\n  formContainer: // the wrapping form if you have any and want to have submit buttons or clear button (optional)\n  searchAsYouType: true/false (default to true)\n});\n```\n\nOnce a formContainer is passed, we should listen for reset and submit events on it if needed.\n\nWe would need to stop documenting `searchOnlyOnEnterKey..` and `container` for this widget, even if they should keep working.\n",
  "created_at": "2016-02-18T08:58:26Z",
